# Model Gates (pre-edit + post-change)

## Pre-edit dispatch (announce-and-go)

**BEFORE any file edit**, state: (1) **Archetype** (2) **Tier** T0–T3 + default model (3) **Dispatch** — inline Composer 2.5 or escalate (4) **Parallel plan** per `parallel-agent-strategy.mdc`.

> **Billing:** Composer 2.5 Fast = orchestrator + default worker (included quota). Sonnet 4.6 = on-demand only.

| Tier | Archetypes | Model |
|------|-----------|-------|
| T0 | `ui-component`, `css-restyle`, `docs-update`, scout/inventory | **Composer 2.5 Fast** (inline) |
| T1 | `multi-file-feature`, `type-refactor`, `service-logic` | **Composer 2.5 Fast** (inline) |
| T2 | multi-file with auth/routing/Firestore reads | **Composer 2.5 Fast** (inline; escalate if uncertain) |
| T3 | `backend-write-critical` (rules, CF writes, schema) | **Composer 2.5 Fast** (inline, trial) — Sonnet security gate before push |

## Platform parity (D-20 — all Composer sessions)

`.cursor/rules/*` **alwaysApply** rules bind **every** Composer session — desktop IDE, mobile Cursor app, and cloud VM — with **identical** harness behavior: ship-loop tiers (`ship-loop.mdc`), repair loop (§ Repair loop), planning verify loop (§ Planning verify loop), **Fable adversarial pairing loop (§ Fable adversarial pairing, D-22)**, verification ladder (§ Verification ladder), security gate (`security-review-gate.mdc`), stall-advisor (D-19), Ship/Critical/Work/Planning/Fable-adversarial verifiers, evidence lines, and fix-closure. Cloud agents read the same rules from the repo; **no "mobile-lite" orchestration**.

**Exceptions** — mobile/cloud differ **only** where physically impossible (e.g. Dan must tap secrets in Cursor Environments UI; branch-only ship when the prompt forbids `main` push). Document exceptions in `AGENTS.md` and `docs/cloud-agent-iphone-setup.md`, not in separate rule files.

## 2-fail diagnose-only rule (Dan 2026-07-03 — authoritative; Grok stall layer D-19)

When **Composer fails twice on the same task**, escalate to **Sonnet 4.6** via Task subagent for diagnosis only (root cause, hypothesis) — **unless** the 2nd fail shares the **same failure fingerprint** as the 1st (then **Grok stall-advisor** runs first; Sonnet when still stuck per sequence below).

- **Only Composer** updates code, runs verify, and completes the ship loop.
- Sonnet = **diagnostic reviewer only** — no commits, no file edits, no ship loop.
- Grok stall-advisor = **advisory only** — hypotheses + next experiments; no commits, no file edits, no ship loop.
- After Sonnet or Grok returns findings, **Composer** implements + verify + ship.

**Counting failures:** implement+verify attempts on the **same task scope** in one session (or continued thread). Security-gate Sonnet runs are separate — not counted.

### Same failure fingerprint (D-19)

Two consecutive fails on the same task scope share a fingerprint when the **normalized failure key** matches:

| Source | Fingerprint key |
|--------|-----------------|
| `verify:*` / `scripts/verify-*.mjs` | script name (or npm script) + first failed assertion or error message (whitespace-normalized; strip timestamps/paths that drift per run) |
| `npm run build` / `tsc` | error code + file + line (e.g. `TS2322:src/foo.ts:42`) |
| Playwright / runtime | test or step name + error class + stable message substring (first 120 chars, normalized) |

**Different fingerprint** on 2nd fail → skip Grok stall-advisor; 2nd fail triggers Sonnet directly.

### Failure sequence (ordered)

1. **1st fail** → Composer retry (+ optional self-trace per `MODEL_DOSSIER.md` tag `composer-trace`).
2. **2nd fail, same fingerprint as 1st** → **Grok stall-advisor** (mandatory; § below) → Composer retry per hypotheses.
3. **Sonnet diagnose-only** (mandatory) when **still stuck** — ANY of:
   - 2nd implement+verify fail where 2nd fingerprint **≠** 1st (Grok skipped);
   - 3rd+ implement+verify fail on same task after Grok stall-advisor ran;
   - `confStart < 70` or Dan says "still broken" without new hypothesis (after 1st-fail self-trace).
4. Composer implements after Sonnet returns.

Other Sonnet triggers: security verifier before push; architecture unclear after synthesis. **Not** for scouts or routine T0/T1/T2 before 1st fail + retry. Opus 4.6 = locked fallback only if Sonnet security gate returns HIGH Composer cannot resolve.

## Grok stall-advisor auto-invoke (Dan 2026-07-10 — D-19)

**Pain event:** Dan 2026-07-10 consecutive same-failure stall — Composer retried identical fixes without a cheap pivot.

Dispatch exactly **one** read-only Task when **2nd consecutive implement+verify fail** on the same task scope shares the **same failure fingerprint** as the 1st:

```text
Task({
  subagent_type: "generalPurpose",
  model: "grok-4.5-fast-xhigh",
  readonly: true,
  description: "Stall advisor",
  prompt: "…symptom, fingerprint, task scope, files touched, prior fix attempts, self-trace block… Return hypotheses + ranked next experiments only — no implementation."
})
```

**Evidence:** completion report MUST include `stall-advisor: <task-id>` + `model: grok-4.5-fast-xhigh`, or `stall-advisor: N/A (fingerprints differed)`. Missing Task id when trigger fired = **NOT RUN**.

**When NOT to invoke:** 1st fail only; 2nd fail with different fingerprint (→ Sonnet per § 2-fail); security-gate Sonnet; post-ship Ship Verifier; Repair Verifier on Dan repair intent; Planning Verifier on planning questions (§ Planning verify loop); Critical Reviewer pre-decision; Dan says skip. **One run per fingerprint per task scope** — 3rd+ same fingerprint after Grok → Sonnet, not a second stall-advisor.

**vs Ship Verifier / Repair Verifier / Planning Verifier:** orthogonal roles — Ship Verifier = post-ship scope check; Repair Verifier = Dan repair-intent pre-close (§ Repair loop); Planning Verifier = pre-present planning accuracy (§ Planning verify loop); stall-advisor = mid-task same-failure pivot. Same model slug; never satisfy both with one Task in the same event.

## Security gate

Invocation, model lock, and evidence requirements: **`security-review-gate.mdc`** (sole authoritative copy). Run **before push** — not after commit. Never self-report PASS from Composer inline review.

## Post-change model audit

After every substantive code/config change, brief audit before reporting done.

**Low-risk exemption:** read-only audits, docs/rules-only → short line OK (e.g. `Model routing: T0 docs/rules; no escalation`).

**Code/config** — compact block:

```
### Model audit
| Change | Archetype | Tier | Worker | Scouts parallel? | Escalation review? | Verdict |
```

When security gate triggered: `security-gate-id: <uuid>`, `model: claude-4.6-sonnet-medium-thinking`, `actual model invocation evidence: yes/no/unknown`, `verdict: PASS|MEDIUM|HIGH|NOT RUN`. No UUID → **NOT RUN**, not PASS.

Complete ship loop (`ship-loop.mdc`) before declaring done for code/config changes.

## Verification ladder (Dan 2026-07-08 — authoritative)

| Tier | Actor | Role | Auto-invoked |
|------|-------|------|--------------|
| 0 (free) | Composer 2.5 + scripts | Builder + mechanical checks: build, `away:validate`, `verify:*`, diff-vs-scope paths, mandatory report lines | Always (existing behavior) |
| 1 (cheap) | Grok 4.5 Fast — **Ship Verifier** | Post-ship scope/correctness + missed-security-gate check | After EVERY substantive ship (§ below) |
| 1b (cheap) | Grok 4.5 Fast — **Stall Advisor** | Mid-task same-failure pivot — hypotheses + next experiments only | 2nd consecutive same fingerprint on same task (§ Grok stall-advisor) |
| 1c (cheap) | Grok 4.5 Fast — **Repair Verifier** | Pre-close repair scope/result on Dan repair intent | Dan says repair/fix/debug/try again/correct this (§ Repair loop) |
| 1d (cheap) | Grok 4.5 Fast — **Planning Verifier** | Pre-present accuracy of planning/roadmap/queue answers | Planning question triggers (§ Planning verify loop) |
| 2 (security) | Sonnet 4.6 | Security gate per `security-review-gate.mdc` — unchanged | Existing triggers, PLUS Ship Verifier flags a security-relevant diff shipped without `security-gate-id` |
| 3 (rare) | Fable 5 — **Work Verifier** | Deep verification: spec phase boundaries, escalations, Dan-invoked | Fable-spec phase boundary; Ship Verifier escalates ambiguity/architecture; Dan says "fable verify" |
| 3↔1 (pair) | Grok 4.5 Fast — **Fable Adversarial** | Adversarial review of every Fable deep spec/architecture answer | **Always** immediately after Work Verifier or any Fable architecture/spec output (§ Fable adversarial pairing, D-22) |

Evidence standard (every tier): Task id + model line in the report, else **NOT RUN**.

## Fix-closure rule (universal — Dan 2026-07-08)

When any verifier/reviewer model (Repair Verifier/Grok, Planning Verifier/Grok, Ship Verifier/Grok, security gate/Sonnet, Work Verifier/Fable, **Fable Adversarial/Grok**, Critical Reviewer/Grok on blocking findings) reports an issue and Composer applies fixes, the **SAME model re-verifies before the finding closes** — in every context (interactive, away, overnight). One re-verify cycle per existing loop bounds; still failing → escalate per that role's rule. Composer self-attesting "fixed" NEVER closes a finding. Evidence: the completion report must include `fix-verified: <re-verify task-id>` (same-model) for every closed finding; a finding without it stays OPEN and blocks the next ship per the Ship Verifier blocking rule.

### Repair loop (Dan 2026-07-11 — extends § Fix-closure rule)

**Trigger:** Dan expresses explicit **repair intent** on broken behavior — e.g. repair, fix, debug, try again, correct this (or equivalent steering to correct already-broken behavior, not greenfield build).

**Flow:** dispatch routed verifier → FAIL → Composer fix only → **same verifier** re-verify per § Fix-closure rule → repeat until PASS. **Max 3 fix cycles** (initial verify + up to 3 Composer fix→re-verify rounds) then escalate Dan. Composer never self-closes a verifier finding.

| Repair class | Verifier model | Task type |
|---|---|---|
| UI / verify script / logic (default) | Grok 4.5 Fast | `generalPurpose`, `readonly`, `model: grok-4.5-fast-xhigh` |
| 2nd consecutive same failure fingerprint (D-19) | Grok stall-advisor first; Sonnet diagnose-only if still stuck | unchanged § 2-fail / Grok stall-advisor |
| Security / auth / rules / CF touched in repair | Sonnet 4.6 | `security-review`, `model: claude-4.6-sonnet-medium-thinking` per `security-review-gate.mdc` |
| Fable-spec phase or architecture ambiguity | Fable 5 | `work-verifier` per § Work Verifier |

**Dispatch (default repair verifier — Grok):**

```text
Task({
  subagent_type: "generalPurpose",
  model: "grok-4.5-fast-xhigh",
  readonly: true,
  description: "Repair verifier",
  prompt: "…repair scope, symptom, files touched, verify evidence… PASS/FAIL + exact fix list if FAIL."
})
```

**Evidence (mandatory on repair completion):** `repair-verifier: <task-id>` + `model:` line; `fix-verified: <re-verify task-id>` per closed finding. Missing Task id when trigger fired = **NOT RUN** — repair not done.

**Orthogonal roles:** Repair verifier = mid-task scope/result on Dan repair intent; Ship Verifier = post-ship; stall-advisor = same-failure pivot (D-19). Same Grok slug; dispatch per context — never satisfy repair + ship + stall with one Task unless explicitly same scope.

**Platform parity:** Repair loop follows § Platform parity (D-20) — same verifier routing (Grok / Sonnet / Fable via `Task`), same evidence lines (`repair-verifier:`, `fix-verified:`), same max 3 fix cycles, same fix-closure on all clients; Composer never self-closes a repair finding. Missing Task id on repair completion = **NOT RUN** — repair not done — regardless of client.

### Planning verify loop (Dan 2026-07-11 — extends § Fix-closure rule)

**Trigger phrases** — Dan asks any planning/priority question, including:
- "what's next" / "what's next to build?"
- "what else can be worked on?" / "what can we work on?"
- roadmap / priority / queue planning / ranked options
- away planning (Plan → Approve → Queue — not away **execute**)

**Flow:** scouts per `parallel-agent-strategy.mdc` § Planning question protocol → Composer synthesizes draft → dispatch **Planning Verifier** → PARTIAL/FAIL → Composer revises draft only → **same verifier** re-verify per § Fix-closure rule → repeat until PASS. **Max 3 cycles** (initial verify + up to 2 Composer revise→re-verify rounds); then present with **`Caveat: planning-verifier exhausted`**. **Only present Dan the Grok-PASS answer** (or exhausted caveat). Composer never self-closes a planning finding.

**Verifier:** Grok 4.5 Fast — one Task per revision cycle:

```text
Task({
  subagent_type: "generalPurpose",
  model: "grok-4.5-fast-xhigh",
  readonly: true,
  description: "Planning verifier",
  prompt: "…planning question, synthesized draft, scout sources cited… Cross-check: CURRENT_STATE wins over roadmap; away:next head; no invented away IDs; recent main commits/ships not omitted; prod verify caveats; tier/approval gates accurate; known gotchas (e.g. hideSeedDemoRows). PASS | PARTIAL | FAIL + exact fix list if not PASS."
})
```

**Grok checks (mandatory):** `CURRENT_STATE.md` wins over `docs/roadmap.md`; `npm run away:next -- --minimal` queue head; no invented away IDs; recent ships not omitted; prod verify caveats; tier/approval gates accurate; known gotchas from `gotcha-map.json` (e.g. `hideSeedDemoRows`).

**Evidence (mandatory on planning answers):** `planning-verifier: <task-id>` + `model: grok-4.5-fast-xhigh` + verdict **PASS** required before present; `fix-verified: <re-verify task-id>` when Grok flagged issues and Composer revised. Missing Task id when trigger fired = **NOT RUN** — do not present ranked options.

**Orthogonal roles:** Planning verifier = pre-present planning/roadmap/queue accuracy; Repair verifier = Dan repair intent; Ship Verifier = post-ship; stall-advisor = same-failure pivot (D-19); Critical Reviewer = pre-decision on new gates/architecture. Same Grok slug; dispatch per context — never satisfy planning + repair + ship + stall with one Task unless explicitly same scope.

**Platform parity:** Planning verify loop follows § Platform parity (D-20/D-21) — same verifier routing, evidence lines, max 3 cycles, fix-closure on desktop, mobile Cursor, and cloud VM; Composer never self-closes a planning finding.

## Ship Verifier auto-invoke (Grok — Dan 2026-07-08)

**Substantive ship (path-classified — NEVER by commit message prefix):** any pushed commit(s) touching `src/`, `functions/src/`, `public/`, `index.html`, or behavior-bearing `scripts/*.mjs` — even if labeled `chore:`. Excluded: commits touching only `docs/`, `PROJECT_STATUS/`, `.cursor/`, README, or compiled `functions/lib` sync-only. Multi-commit ships (feature + fix in one session) = ONE verification covering the full range.

**Dispatch + evidence:** after push, the conversation that shipped dispatches exactly ONE read-only Task (`subagent_type: "generalPurpose"`, `model: "grok-4.5-fast-xhigh"`, `readonly: true`). Completion report MUST include `ship-verifier: <task-id>` or `ship-verifier: N/A (paths excluded)` — missing line = NOT RUN. **Blocking:** the next substantive ship in any conversation is blocked while a prior ship's verification is NOT RUN or has an unresolved FAIL — check CURRENT_STATE blockers.

**Loop bounds:** PASS → done. FAIL → exact fix list (file:line, required change, why) → Composer fixes → same-model re-verify per § Fix-closure rule → still failing → escalate to Fable (ambiguity/architecture) or Dan (everything else). **Security:** Ship Verifier never judges security — it directs Composer to invoke the Sonnet gate; Sonnet closes its own findings per § Fix-closure rule.

## Critical Reviewer auto-invoke (Grok — Dan 2026-07-08)

Dispatch exactly ONE read-only Task (`subagent_type: "generalPurpose"`, `model: "grok-4.5-fast-xhigh"`, `readonly: true`) BEFORE finalizing or presenting, when ANY of:

- New `.cursor/rules/` file, or an edit changing >30 lines of an existing rule/protocol file
- A plan with ≥3 phases or touching ≥5 files is about to be presented for approval
- A new gate, model role, subagent lane, or recurring workflow is being proposed
- An architecture decision with ≥2 competing options is being put to Dan
- Dan says "grok review" or "devil's advocate"

Never auto-invoke for: routine code/UI edits, bug fixes, deploys, security review (Sonnet owns it), rule tweaks ≤10 lines, executing an already-reviewed plan, or when § Fable adversarial pairing already ran Grok on the same architecture output (D-22). One run per decision — rerun only on material plan change. Evidence: completion report must cite the Task id + model line (same standard as security gate) or the review = NOT RUN. Full role spec: `MODEL_DOSSIER.md` tag `critical-reviewer`.

**Freeze check (D-16):** before approving any new gate, role, workflow, or abstraction, verify the proposal against `PROJECT_STATUS/HARNESS_V1_FREEZE.md` reopening criteria and apply the D-14 evidence-pairing and D-15 deletion/80-20 tests.

## Work Verifier auto-invoke (Fable 5 — tier 3 only, Dan 2026-07-08)

Dispatch exactly ONE read-only Task (`model: "claude-fable-5-thinking-high"`) ONLY when: (1) a phase of a Fable-authored product/architecture spec with semantic drift tripwires completes — before phase N+1 (spec's own gate note, e.g. `docs/location-first-transition-spec.md`, is authoritative); (2) the Ship Verifier escalates ambiguity/architecture concerns; (3) Dan says "fable verify" / "fable check". NOT per-ship (Ship Verifier owns that), NOT for mechanical checklist phases, away batches, routine T2+, or red-gate diagnosis (Sonnet 2-fail owns that). Fix loop: § Fix-closure rule (1 cycle, then Dan). Spec-phase completion reports MUST include a `work-verifier:` line — Task id, or `NOT RUN — phase N+1 blocked until it runs`. Full spec: `MODEL_DOSSIER.md` tag `work-verifier`.

**Verify-only (Dan 2026-07-09):** Fable never edits files, commits, or runs the ship loop — same standing as Sonnet diagnose-only. Only Composer 2.5 implements; Fable verifies Composer's work. When Fable finds issues: Composer fixes, Fable re-verifies per § Fix-closure; affected work ships only after Fable confirms correct.

**Pairing (D-22):** Every Work Verifier run **must** be followed immediately by § Fable adversarial pairing on the same Fable output — mobile, desktop, and cloud; missing `fable-adversarial:` = NOT RUN for spec/architecture present.

## Fable adversarial pairing loop (Dan 2026-07-11 — D-22)

**Purpose:** Grok 4.5 Fast is the **mandatory adversarial second opinion** on every Fable 5 deep spec, architecture, or escalation answer — before Dan sees the recommendation or Composer implements harness/product design from it. Fable proposes; Grok attacks. Same pairing on **mobile Cursor, cloud VM, and desktop** (§ Platform parity, D-20).

**Triggers — dispatch Fable first, then Grok adversarial on Fable's return:**

1. **Work Verifier** fired (§ Work Verifier) — spec phase boundary, Ship Verifier architecture escalation, Dan says "fable verify" / "fable check"
2. Dan asks Fable (or orchestrator routes to Fable) for **deep spec, architecture, harness design, or convergence** — e.g. autonomy lanes, location-first phase gates, away protocol changes
3. **Repair loop** routes to Fable for spec-phase or architecture ambiguity (§ Repair loop table)
4. Ship Verifier escalates ambiguity/architecture → Fable answers → Grok adversarial on that answer

**Never pair for:** routine T0/T1/T2 implementation without Fable; planning questions (§ Planning verify loop owns Grok-only); security gate (Sonnet); mechanical checklist phases; away batch per-item code unless Fable was invoked for design.

**Flow (ordered — do not present until Grok PASS or exhausted caveat):**

1. Dispatch **Fable** (`claude-fable-5-thinking-high`, `readonly`) → capture full output (recommendations, schema proposals, gates).
2. Dispatch **Fable Adversarial** Grok (`grok-4.5-fast-xhigh`, `readonly`) with Fable output + authoritative sources (`HARNESS_V1_FREEZE.md`, `DECISIONS.md`, away SSOT, spec tripwires). Grok must: **REJECT** / **KEEP** / **ACCEPT** list; freeze check (D-16); SSOT corruption scan; converged protocol if applicable.
3. **PARTIAL/FAIL** → Fable rebuttal or Composer revises synthesis → **same Grok** re-verifies per § Fix-closure. **Max 3 cycles** (initial adversarial + up to 2 convergence rounds); then present with **`Caveat: fable-adversarial exhausted`**.
4. **PASS** → present converged answer only (single "Composer findings" block when both models agree).

**Dispatch (Fable Adversarial — Grok):**

```text
Task({
  subagent_type: "generalPurpose",
  model: "grok-4.5-fast-xhigh",
  readonly: true,
  description: "Fable adversarial",
  prompt: "…Fable output verbatim, task scope, authoritative sources… Adversarial review: REJECT/KEEP/ACCEPT; freeze D-16; away/built SSOT; hidden schema/gates; converged protocol; verdict PASS|PARTIAL|FAIL + exact fixes if not PASS."
})
```

**Grok checks (mandatory):** `HARNESS_V1_FREEZE.md` 2× pain bar; `away-validate` / `built` semantics; no schema-by-stealth; no new gates without pain; contradictions with `DECISIONS.md` and existing alwaysApply rules; D-15 deletion test on Fable additions.

**Evidence (mandatory when pairing triggered):** `work-verifier: <fable-task-id>` — **required real Fable Task id**; paraphrased "Fable said" without Task dispatch = NOT RUN, route to Critical Reviewer instead — plus `fable-adversarial: <grok-task-id>` + `model: grok-4.5-fast-xhigh` + verdict **PASS** required before present/implement design; `fix-verified: <re-verify task-id>` when Grok flagged issues and Fable/Composer revised. Missing `fable-adversarial:` when Fable Task ran on spec/architecture = **NOT RUN** — do not present design or edit rules from Fable alone.

**vs Critical Reviewer:** When this pairing runs on an architecture/harness decision, the Grok adversarial pass **satisfies** § Critical Reviewer for that same Fable answer — do not dispatch a second Grok Critical Reviewer on identical output in the same turn. Critical Reviewer still runs standalone when **no Fable output** exists (new gate proposal from Composer only, ≥3-phase plan from Composer draft, Dan says "grok review").

**Platform parity:** Identical pairing on desktop IDE, mobile Cursor app, and cloud VM; no mobile skip. Composer never self-closes a Fable-adversarial finding.
